# Database Rules — Drizzle ORM + Supabase

## Core Principle
ALL database interactions MUST use the Drizzle schema and Drizzle query/mutation APIs.
No exceptions.

## Schema Location
- All table definitions live in `src/db/schema/` as Drizzle `pgTable` calls
- Barrel export: `src/db/schema/index.ts` — always import schema from here
- DB client: `src/db/index.ts` — exports the `db` instance with all schema loaded

### Current Tables
- `decks` — `src/db/schema/decks.ts` (columns: id, userId, title, description, createdAt, updatedAt, deletedAt)
- `cards` — `src/db/schema/cards.ts` (columns: id, deckId, front, back, position, createdAt, updatedAt, deletedAt)

## Mandatory Patterns

### Always use Drizzle typed queries
```ts
// CORRECT — use db with schema imports
import { db } from '@/db'
import { decks, cards } from '@/db/schema'
import { eq, and, isNull } from 'drizzle-orm'

const result = await db.select({
  id: decks.id,
  title: decks.title,
}).from(decks).where(and(eq(decks.userId, userId), isNull(decks.deletedAt)))
```

### Never use raw SQL
```ts
// WRONG — never do this
await db.execute(sql`SELECT * FROM decks WHERE user_id = ${userId}`)
// WRONG — never use postgres client directly
await client.query('SELECT * FROM decks')
// WRONG — never use Supabase client for data queries
const { data } = await supabase.from('decks').select('*')
```

### Never use `SELECT *` — always select explicit columns
```ts
// WRONG
await db.select().from(decks)

// CORRECT
await db.select({ id: decks.id, title: decks.title, description: decks.description }).from(decks)
```

### Use inferred types from schema — never duplicate
```ts
// CORRECT — use Drizzle inferred types
import { type Deck, type NewDeck } from '@/db/schema/decks'
import { type Card, type NewCard } from '@/db/schema/cards'

// WRONG — never manually redefine table shapes
interface Deck { id: string; title: string; ... }
```

## Schema Standards

### Primary Keys
- All tables use `uuid('id').defaultRandom().primaryKey()`

### Timestamps
- `createdAt: timestamp('created_at').defaultNow().notNull()`
- `updatedAt: timestamp('updated_at').defaultNow().notNull()`
- Always set `updatedAt` to `new Date()` on mutations

### Soft Deletes
- `deletedAt: timestamp('deleted_at')` — nullable
- Never hard-delete user data
- Always filter with `isNull(table.deletedAt)` on reads
- Soft delete = `await db.update(table).set({ deletedAt: new Date() }).where(eq(table.id, id))`

### Foreign Keys
- Define with `.references(() => parentTable.id, { onDelete: 'cascade' })` where appropriate
- Add indexes on all foreign key columns

### Relations
- Define with `relations()` from `drizzle-orm` in the same schema file as the table
- Export relations alongside the table definition

## Insert / Update / Delete Patterns

### Insert
```ts
const [newDeck] = await db.insert(decks).values({
  userId,
  title: 'My Deck',
  description: 'A new deck',
}).returning({ id: decks.id, title: decks.title })
```

### Update
```ts
await db.update(decks).set({
  title: 'Updated Title',
  updatedAt: new Date(),
}).where(eq(decks.id, deckId))
```

### Soft Delete
```ts
await db.update(decks).set({
  deletedAt: new Date(),
  updatedAt: new Date(),
}).where(eq(decks.id, deckId))
```

## Adding New Tables

1. Create a new file in `src/db/schema/` (e.g., `progress.ts`)
2. Define the table with `pgTable`, relations, and export inferred types
3. Re-export from `src/db/schema/index.ts`
4. Run `npx drizzle-kit generate` to create the migration
5. Run `npx drizzle-kit migrate` to apply it

## Forbidden Practices
- ❌ No raw SQL strings or `sql` template tags for CRUD operations
- ❌ No `SELECT *` — always specify columns
- ❌ No Supabase JS client (`supabase.from(...)`) for data reads/writes — use Drizzle
- ❌ No manual type definitions that mirror table shapes — use `$inferSelect` / `$inferInsert`
- ❌ No `any` in query results
- ❌ No hard deletes on user data
- ❌ No database queries in React components — queries belong in server actions or API routes
- ❌ No storing Stripe secret keys or sensitive tokens in the database without encryption
